Detailed Description

template<template< size_t > class ValueType = PartialSymbolicSemantics::ValueType>
class BinaryAnalysis::InstructionSemantics::PartialSymbolicSemantics::MemoryCell< ValueType >

Memory cell with partially symbolic address and data.

The ValueType template argument should be a subclass of PartialSymbolicSemantics::ValueType.

Member Function Documentation

template<template< size_t > class ValueType>
bool BinaryAnalysis::InstructionSemantics::PartialSymbolicSemantics::MemoryCell< ValueType >::may_alias ( const MemoryCell< ValueType > &  other  )  const

Returns true if this memory value could possibly overlap with the other memory value.

In other words, returns false only if this memory location cannot overlap with other memory location. Two addresses that are identical alias one another.

bool BinaryAnalysis::InstructionSemantics::PartialSymbolicSemantics::MemoryCell< ValueType >::must_alias ( const MemoryCell< ValueType > &  other  )  const

Returns true if this memory address is the same as the other.

Note that "same" is more strict than "overlap".
